ip] (in Tanzania) and other dialects. Minor dialect differences between Mambwe and Lungu.  Classification: Niger-Congo,  Atlantic-Congo,  Volta-Congo,  Benue-Congo,  Bantoid,  Southern,  Narrow Bantu,  Central,  F,  Tongwe (F.10) |Mashi| 20, 800| in Zambia (1969 census). Population total all countries: 23, 630. Southwest Western Province. Also in Angola,  Namibia. Alternate names: Masi.  Dialects: North Kwandu,  South Kwandu,  Mashi. A dalect subgroup.  Classification: Niger-Congo,  Atlantic-Congo,  Volta-Congo,  Benue-Congo,  Bantoid,  Southern,  Narrow Bantu,  Central,  K,  Kwangwa (K.40) |Mbowe| 2, 690| (1969 census). North central Western Province. Alternate names: Esimbowe.  Classification: Niger-Congo,  Atlantic-Congo,  Volta-Congo,  Benue-Congo,  Bantoid,  Southern,  Narrow Bantu,  Central,  K,  Kwangwa (K.40) |Mbukushu| 5, 000 |in Zambia (2006). Western Province,  southwest,  Kwando River area. Alternate names: Gova,  Kusso,  Mambukush,  Mampukush,  Mbukuhu,  Mbukushi,  Thimukushu.  Classification: Niger-Congo,  Atlantic-Congo,  Volta-Congo,  Benue-Congo,  Bantoid,  Southern,  Narrow Bantu,  Central,  K,  Kwangwa (K.40) |Mbunda| 156, 000| in Zambia (2006). Population total all countries: 291, 000. West Northwestern Province,  north Barotseland. Also in Angola. Alternate names: Chimbunda,  Gimbunda,  Kimbunda,  Mbuunda.  Classification: Niger-Congo,  Atlantic-Congo,  Volta-Congo,  Benue-Congo,  Bantoid,  Southern,  Narrow Bantu,  Central,  K,  Chokwe-Luchazi (K.20) |Nkoya| 146, 000| (2006). Western and Southern provinces,  Mankoya area. Alternate names: Shinkoya.  Dialects: Nkoya,  Mbowela (Mbwela,  Mbwera,  Shimbwera),  Lushangi,  Shasha,  Lukolwe,  Mashasha.  Classification: Niger-Congo,  Atlantic-Congo,  Volta-Congo,  Benue-Congo,  Bantoid,  Southern,  Narrow Bantu,  Central,  L,  Nkoya (L.50) |Nsenga| 544, 000| in Zambia (2006). Population total all countries: 752, 100. Eastern and Central provinces,  Petauke District. Also in Mozambique,  Zimbabwe. Alter